<subSubSection lastPageNumber="360" pageNumber="359" type="discussion">
<paragraph lastPageNumber="360" pageNumber="359">
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="359">Note:</emphasis>
Grant &amp; Zijlstra (in 
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="359">Selbyana</emphasis>
19: 96. 1998) argue that 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityYear="1753" class="Liliopsida" family="Bromeliaceae" genus="Bromelia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="karatas">
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="359">B. karatas</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is the 
<typeStatus>generitype</typeStatus>
, the choice having been made by Regel (in 
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="359">Gartenflora</emphasis>
17: 67. 1868) which therefore pre-dates the choice of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityYear="1753" class="Liliopsida" family="Bromeliaceae" genus="Bromelia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="pinguin">
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="359">B.</emphasis>
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="360">pinguin</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
made by Hitchcock (
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="360">Prop. Brit. Bot.</emphasis>
: 144. 1929). See discussion of the species name by Smith (in 
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="360">Phytologia</emphasis>
15: 173. 1967) who noted that 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Linnaeusâ€™">Linnaeus'</normalizedToken>
&quot;panicula diffusa&quot; is not shown by the cited Plumier element to which the name had long been attached. Espejo-Serna &amp; al. (in 
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="360">Selbyana</emphasis>
25: 39. 2004) indicated &quot; 
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="360">C. Plumier s.n.</emphasis>
(LINN)&quot; as the 
<typeStatus>holotype</typeStatus>
but there is no such material present in LINN.
</paragraph>
